Fred Emney Sr https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fred_Emney_Sr 0 Frederick Charles Emney (1865 – 7 January 1917), known professionally as Fred Emney, was an English comedian, known for his appearances in farce, comic opera, musical comedy, music hall and pantomime. He was a member of a theatrical family: among his uncles was the popular comedian Arthur Williams, and he was the father of Fred Emney, a comic character actor frequently seen on stage and screen in the mid-20th century.
